  "prompt": "How long can I stay outside the UK as a dependant of the tier2 visa?",
  "response": "For dependants of tier 2 visa holders in the UK, there's no specific maximum period mentioned for staying outside the UK. However, the key thing to remember is that absences should not impact your ability to qualify for Indefinite Leave to Remain (ILR) in the future, which usually requires the main applicant and their dependants to have lived continuously in the UK for five years.\n\nHere are some important considerations:\n1. **Continuous Residence**: For ILR, continuous residence generally means not being outside the UK for more than 180 days in any 12-month period during the qualifying period (usually five years).\n   \n2. **Documenting Absences**: If you do have to stay outside the UK for any significant period, it's crucial to maintain records and reasons for your absences.\n\nAlways check the latest UK Visas and Immigration (UKVI) guidelines or consult with an immigration advisor for personalized advice as rules and interpretations can change.",
